cess to funds. This provision gives policyholders control over their financial decisions and allows them to convert the policy’s accumulated value into a lump sum [Data: Entities (40), Relationships (39, 61, 65, 66, +more)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Reduced benefit upon premium lapse after two years\",\n            \"explanation\": \"If the policyholder stops paying premiums after two years, the policy continues with a reduced death benefit based on the accumulated cash value. This feature acts as a safety net, allowing coverage to remain active even during periods of financial hardship. The reduced benefit is determined by the available cash value, which is used to maintain the policy on a lower coverage basis. This mechanism ensures that the policyholder does not lose all protection immediately upon missing payments, preserving some level of financial security [Data: Entities (55), Relationships (61, 38, 39, 65, 66, +more)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Reinstatement of a lapsed policy within a two-year window\",\n            \"explanation\": \"The RESTART POLICY provision allows policyholders to reinstate their insurance coverage within a two-year window following a lapse. This option is designed to provide financial relief to individuals who missed premium payments due to temporary hardship or oversight. To reinstate the policy, the policyholder must pay all missed premiums plus applicable interest, calculated from the original due dates. This reinstatement process restores the original policy terms, including coverage benefits and guarantees, without requiring a new application or underwriting [Data: Entities (51), Relationships (65, 66, 38, 39, 61, +more)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Interest on missed premiums during reinstatement\",\n            \"explanation\": \"When restarting a lapsed policy within the two-year window, interest is applied to the missed premiums. This interest c